{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"Header 1": "Problem 27:"}, "page_content": "Here is a clear and concise explanation you can use for your documentation, code comments, or pull request description to justify the approach:  \n### **Why this approach was used in NotificationScreen.tsx**  \nIn **NotificationScreen.tsx**, the text inside the section headers (specifically 'Earlier', 'Yesterday', and 'Received') was not aligning correctly with the rest of the list content.  \nBecause the SectionHeader component is shared across multiple screens in the project, modifying its internal padding directly carried a high risk of breaking layouts on other pages. To safely fix the alignment for this specific screen without causing unintended global side effects, the SectionHeader was wrapped in a local &lt;View&gt; to apply the necessary horizontal padding.  \n**Code Snippet:**  \nTypeScript  \n&lt;View style={{ paddingHorizontal: theme.spacing.md }}&gt;  \n&lt;SectionHeader title=\"Earlier\" theme={theme} /&gt;  \n&lt;/View&gt;", "type": "Document"}}